main event: A sighting of an object identified as JUPITER at 0710Z at 260 degrees azimuth and 25 degrees elevation.
interesting points: The object had white, flash red, orange, and green lights.
The object was sighted at 25 degrees azimuth, but it was not moving and did not disappear.
The sighting lasted for about 25 minutes.
The report was from a military source in Klamath, Oregon.
The conclusion was that the object was ASTRO(JUPITER).
sighted object: A single object with white, flash red, orange, and green lights
